
                                            BLSA remains open to working with Eskom but this does not mean that it's reconsidering the suspension.

                                         JOHANNESBURG - Business Leadership South Africa (BLSA) says Eskom’s suspension will not be lifted until serious allegations against the power utility have been addressed. BLSA says its met with the new acting CEO Sean Maritz to explore Eskom’s commitment to addressing governance issues and the organisation remains open to working with the state-owned company. But this does not mean that it's reconsidering the suspension. The organisation's Themba Maseko said: “We remain committed to our initial call that the board of Eskom needs to be restructured and the management team needs to be strengthened.”